---
description: "Guidelines for using notes with todo.ai tasks"
alwaysApply: true
---
When creating or working with todo.ai tasks, add notes to provide implementation context. **NEVER use notes for status updates or completion summaries on parent tasks.**

**Command:** `./todo.ai note <task-id> "Your note here"`

**What to put in notes:**
- Implementation details (file paths, line numbers, function names)
- Dependencies between tasks
- References to documentation or code
- Technical decisions or approach

**What NOT to put in notes:**
- ❌ Status updates ("✅ Task X completed")
- ❌ Completion summaries listing what subtasks are done
- ❌ Progress reports ("3 of 5 subtasks complete")
- ❌ Duplicates of subtask information that's already visible

**Examples:**
- ✅ `./todo.ai note 42 "Modify archive_task() lines 2600-2850. Pattern from delete_task() lines 2926-2935"`
- ✅ `./todo.ai note 42.1 "Depends on task#42 completing first - needs collect_notes() function"`
- ✅ `./todo.ai note 50 "See docs/analysis/CODE_SIZE_ANALYSIS.md lines 66-67 for migration cleanup details"`
- ❌ `./todo.ai note 42 "Fix it"` - Too vague, no actionable context
- ❌ `./todo.ai note 42 "✅ #42.1 done, ✅ #42.2 done, ✅ #42.3 done"` - Status updates belong in subtasks, not notes

**The subtasks show completion status - don't duplicate it in notes!**
